commit.message:
Try to read undefined length values as encapsulated pixel data (#1141)

* Add test with failing read of embedded sequence delimiter

* Remove unused read_undefined_length_value call

* Avoid retrimming bytes leading up to delimiter

* Try to read undefined length values as encapsulated pixel data (#1140)

Allows reading of values that have embedded sequence delimiter items.
Parses the data by seeking from sequence item to sequence item and
eventually reading the entire value in one chunk, rather than reading
smaller chunks and joining together.
When the input data is not properly structured, falls back to scanning
byte by byte for the value delimiter.
